00:00:03.590 --> 00:00:07.200
How to Get Knots out of Your Back.

00:00:07.200 --> 00:00:10.910
Myofascial pain, or pain from muscle knots,
affects 1 in 3 people.

00:00:10.910 --> 00:00:15.250
You can get the knots out using a few simple
methods and be able to get on with your day,

00:00:15.250 --> 00:00:16.250
pain-free.

00:00:16.250 --> 00:00:26.590
You will need Chair Heating pad Sock Rice
Microwave Tennis ball Friend and massage therapist.

00:00:26.590 --> 00:00:27.970
Step 1.

00:00:27.970 --> 00:00:30.140
Massage your supraspinatus muscle.

00:00:30.140 --> 00:00:34.760
Sit in a chair, put your right hand down to
your side, and hold onto the chair's seat.

00:00:34.760 --> 00:00:38.410
Tilt your head to your left and, with your
left hand, reach up to your right shoulder

00:00:38.410 --> 00:00:39.840
and massage the muscle.

00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:41.219
Step 2.

00:00:41.219 --> 00:00:43.050
Switch to the other side.

00:00:43.050 --> 00:00:47.469
Hold the chair with your left hand, tilt your
head to the right, and massage the supraspinatus

00:00:47.469 --> 00:00:48.850
muscle on your left side.

00:00:48.850 --> 00:00:53.460
2 to 3 minutes per hour is all it takes to
work out the knots.

00:00:53.460 --> 00:00:54.850
Step 3.

00:00:54.850 --> 00:00:58.790
Apply a heating pad to the knot to relax the
muscle for 30 minutes at a time.

00:00:58.790 --> 00:01:03.250
You can make a heating pad yourself by filling
a sock with uncooked rice, putting it in the

00:01:03.250 --> 00:01:06.960
microwave for a few minutes, and applying
the hot sock to the knot.

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:07.960
Step 4.

00:01:07.960 --> 00:01:09.759
Use a tennis ball to loosen knots.

00:01:09.759 --> 00:01:12.420
Lie down on the floor with your legs extended.

00:01:12.420 --> 00:01:15.969
Lean on the side with the knot and position
the tennis ball beneath the knotted area.

00:01:15.969 --> 00:01:20.069
Then squirm on the floor, rolling the ball
around until it is directly against the most

00:01:20.069 --> 00:01:21.069
painful area.

00:01:21.069 --> 00:01:25.200
When the ball is in position, wiggle a bit
and allow your body to sink onto the tennis

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:26.200
ball.

00:01:26.200 --> 00:01:28.119
Stay on the ball until the knot is relaxed.

00:01:28.119 --> 00:01:29.270
Step 5.

00:01:29.270 --> 00:01:33.109
Have someone else massage the muscle by standing
behind you while you're sitting, squeezing

00:01:33.109 --> 00:01:37.499
the muscle, and breaking up the kinks and
spasms in the muscle.

00:01:37.499 --> 00:01:38.740
Step 6.

00:01:38.740 --> 00:01:43.279
See a massage therapist to locate and massage
the trigger points of myofascial pain.

00:01:43.279 --> 00:01:47.710
A trained massage therapist will easily work
out the knots that are causing you discomfort.

00:01:47.710 --> 00:01:51.529
The knots will shrink and soon you'll be able
to relax without the nagging irritation of

00:01:51.529 --> 00:01:52.719
back and neck pain.

00:01:52.719 --> 00:01:58.560
Did you know Back pain is the leading cause
of disability in Americans under 45 years

00:01:58.560 --> 00:01:59.220
old.

